# .rscignore — shinyapps.io (rsconnect) deployment exclusions
#
# IMPORTANT: rsconnect matches each line as an EXACT name via setdiff(), applied
# per directory level. It does NOT support globs (e.g. *.md), gitignore syntax,
# trailing-slash directory markers, or path entries like data/score.csv.
# Each line must exactly equal a ROOT-level file or directory name.
# To exclude files inside a subdirectory, put a separate .rscignore there
# (see data/.rscignore).
#
# NOTE: credentials/ is intentionally NOT excluded — required for Google Sheets auth.

# --- Root-level docs ---
CLAUDE.md
ADMIN_INFO.md
README.md
LICENSE

# --- Dev/tooling/knowledge dirs not needed at runtime ---
# .claude: Claude Code config/skills
# docs: project documentation
# knowledge: symlink to an external kaizen knowledge base (must not be deployed)
.claude
docs
knowledge

# --- Stray editor/backup files currently present at root ---
.server.R.swp
ur.R.bak
